title: mobile/android: Only invalid neighbours on mainnet

body:
I have the same issue.

I also put the [enodes of main net](https://gist.github.com/rfikki/416066c9923f3d7277d8f6456c1f880a)  into ``` /storage/emulated/0/Download/ETH/mainChain/GethDroid/static-nodes.json```, and I know they are live nodes by [ethernodes.org](https://www.ethernodes.org/node/0da5e1f5c2c7f35b745554d18d5c44cef3fd01b62c87c24ef7e7eab3c46d7eddeb2d44899dc5aa9fe6fb2d34a1a7f926a44dc3cfa261b6ee8a5548e666ee78ab). But it is still not work. I think the reason is these nodes are not light server(```--lightserv```). Can I have the enodes of light server?

**System information**
Geth version: 1.7.1 and 1.7.3
OS & device: Android 7.0 (Samsung Galaxy S8)

**Expected**
It can connect to main net as soon as possible.

**Actual**
It cannot connect to main net, just trying whole day.
(It can connect to my private chain quickly.)

**Node config**
```java
NodeConfig result = Geth.newNodeConfig();
result.setEthereumNetworkID(1);
result.setEthereumGenesis(Geth.mainnetGenesis());
result.setEthereumDatabaseCache(512);
result.setMaxPeers(10);
result.setBootstrapNodes(Geth.foundationBootnodes());
result.setEthereumEnabled(true);
result.setWhisperEnabled(true);
```
> most of codes are clone from [Mobile Clients: Libraries and Inproc Ethereum Nodes](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Mobile-Clients:-Libraries-and-Inproc-Ethereum-Nodes)
